STEP|51|Use lm-evaluation-harness when:**
STEP|52|Benchmarking models for academic papers
STEP|53|Comparing model quality across standard tasks
STEP|54|Tracking training progress
STEP|55|Reporting standardized metrics (everyone uses same prompts)
STEP|56|Need reproducible evaluation
STEP|57|Use alternatives instead:**
STEP|58|**HELM** (Stanford): Broader evaluation (fairness, efficiency, calibration)
STEP|59|**AlpacaEval**: Instruction-following evaluation with LLM judges
STEP|60|**MT-Bench**: Conversational multi-turn evaluation
STEP|61|**Custom scripts**: Domain-specific evaluation
STEP|62|Issue: Evaluation too slow**
STEP|63|num_fewshot 0 # Instead of 5
STEP|64|tasks mmlu_stem # Only STEM subjects
STEP|65|Issue: Out of memory**
STEP|66|batch_size 1 # Or --batch_size auto
STEP|67|model_args pretrained=model-name,load_in_8bit=True
STEP|68|model_args pretrained=model-name,device_map=auto,offload_folder=offload
STEP|69|Issue: Different results than reported**
STEP|70|num_fewshot 5 # Most papers use 5-shot
STEP|71|tasks mmlu # Not mmlu_direct or mmlu_fewshot
STEP|72|model_args pretrained=model-name,tokenizer=same-model-name
STEP|73|Issue: HumanEval not executing code**
STEP|74|Benchmark descriptions**: See [references/benchmark-guide.md](references/benchmark-guide.md) for detailed description of all 60+ tasks, what they measure, and interpretation.
STEP|75|Custom tasks**: See [references/custom-tasks.md](references/custom-tasks.md) for creating domain-specific evaluation tasks.
STEP|76|API evaluation**: See [references/api-evaluation.md](references/api-evaluation.md) for evaluating OpenAI, Anthropic, and other API models.
STEP|77|Multi-GPU strategies**: See [references/distributed-eval.md](references/distributed-eval.md) for data parallel and tensor parallel evaluation.
STEP|78|**GPU**: NVIDIA (CUDA 11.8+), works on CPU (very slow)
STEP|79|**VRAM**:
